<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 04 at 3:25PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTH CENTRAL CAMBRIA COUNTY
THROUGH 400 PM EDT...
At 325 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles north of Nanty-Glo, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Northern Cambria, Patton, Hastings, Carrolltown, Colver and Chest
Springs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
